<title type="html"><![CDATA[Referencing Narrations]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1161&amp;p=1227#p1227"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">Referencing Narrations</span></strong><br /><em>By the Muhaddith, Shaykh, Allamaa’ Muhammad Nasir uddeen al-Albaani<br /><br />Translated by Abbas Abu Yahya</em><br /><br />Muhammad Nasir- Deen Al-Albaani (d.1420A.H) -Rahimullaah-said:<br /><br />‘The scholars say: ‘from the blessings of knowledge is referencing every statement to the one who said it.’ Forgery and falsification is kept away through referencing works.<br /><br />The Prophet -sallAllaahu alayhi wa sallam- indicated to this in his saying: ‘The one who makes a statement with that which he was not given is like the one who wears a garment of falsehood.’<br /><br />[Collected by Bukhari &amp; Muslim]<br /><br /><em><span style="color: #0000FF">[Taken from: ‘Kalimah Tayyib’ p.11]</span></em><br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://followingthesunnah.wordpress.com/2014/07/11/referencing-narrations/">https://followingthesunnah.wordpress.co ... arrations/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Tue Feb 28, 2017 11:40 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
